{
  "stem": "4032.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I really don't remember exactly how he perished, my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I just don't remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Many times I lay down and-- and I can't recall exactly what happened to my grandpa.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Of course, my parents, I know, perished and the concentration camps called Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They evacuated them-- all-- the whole city-- whoever was left-- to Chelmno, and there was Judenrein, 'clean of Jews.' No more in the city.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we thought that someday we're going to go to Palestine and build a new life, because we didn't see a big future in Poland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't see too big of a future.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] no-- no possibilities to explore your-- your abilities or whatever.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we thought that some day that England will open the doors and let in more Jews to Palestine, so we can come and build a new life.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I was 19 at that time, so we didn't-- there was no-- no-- no way of getting out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was a couple of guys that went to a Hachshara, which is a-- a movement, because a certain amount of certificates the British government allowed to immigrate.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So a couple of guys from our town went to Israel, and one got killed in the war-- in the war of liberation in Israel.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the other one's still around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, September 1st, the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we knew that there is no good thing to expect.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the Germans came in after eight, 10 days, and they started to intimidate the Jews and do all things that was never to heard of.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were taking a couple of guys in the street and putting on a sign on their chest that I am a black marketeer, and-- which was absolutely not true.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
